{"questionId":"9069854","questionHtml":"<p>Calculate the enthalpy change, Δ<em>H</em>, in kJ mol<sup>–1</sup>, for the reaction between ethanoic&nbsp;acid and sodium hydroxide.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>«<em>n</em>(NaOH)&nbsp;= 0.995 mol dm<sup>–3</sup>&nbsp;x 0.0500 dm<sup>3</sup>&nbsp;=» 0.04975 «mol»</p>\n<p><em><strong>OR</strong></em></p>\n<p>«<em>n</em>(CH<sub>3</sub>COOH)&nbsp;= 1.91 mol dm<sup>–3</sup>&nbsp;x 0.0260 dm<sup>3</sup>&nbsp;=» 0.04966 «mol»</p>\n<p>«Δ<em>H</em>&nbsp;= <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" - \\frac{{2.4\\,{\\text{kJ}}}}{{0.04975\\,{\\text{mol}}}} = \">\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2.4</mn>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>kJ</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>0.04975</mn>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>mol</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n</math></span>»&nbsp;–48 / –49 «kJ mol<sup>–1</sup>»</p>\n<p><em>Award <strong>[2]</strong> for correct final answer.</em></p>\n<p><em>Negative sign is required for M2.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9069854","referenceCode":"17N.2.sl.TZ0.d.ii","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Calculate the enthalpy change, ΔH, in kJ mol–1, for the reaction between ethanoic acid and sodium hydroxide.","paper":"2","level":"sl","questionNumber":"d.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 5: Energetics/thermochemistry","5.1 Measuring energy changes","Core","Topic 1: Stoichiometric relationships","1.2 The mole concept","Core","Topic 1: Stoichiometric relationships","Core","Topic 5: Energetics/thermochemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}